🧠 🏆 UNIVERSAL DEVOPS CHEATSHEET (REAL WORLD)

Forget languages. Follow this 3-step method 👇

🔥 STEP 1: Identify project type (30 seconds)

Run:

ls

Look for:

File	Tech
package.json	Node / React
requirements.txt	Python
pom.xml	Java
go.mod	Go

👉 That’s enough. No deep coding knowledge needed.

🔥 STEP 2: Check if build is required

Open config file:

Node:
"build": "vite build"

👉 YES → build needed

Python:

👉 No build (usually)

Java:

👉 mvn package → build needed

Go:

👉 go build → build needed

🔥 STEP 3: Write BASIC Dockerfile first

👉 Don’t overthink. Start simple:

FROM <base-image>

WORKDIR /app
COPY . .

RUN <install>
CMD <run>
🔥 STEP 4: Build and LET IT FAIL 🔥 (IMPORTANT)
docker build -t app .

👉 Now observe errors.

🧠 ERROR → SOLUTION CHEATSHEET
🔴 Error:
gcc not found
make not found

👉 Fix:

RUN apk add --no-cache build-base
🔴 Error:
python not found
node-gyp error

👉 Fix:

RUN apk add --no-cache python3
🔴 Error:
git not found

👉 Fix:

RUN apk add --no-cache git
🔴 Error:
libffi.so not found

👉 Fix:

RUN apk add --no-cache libffi-dev
🔴 Error:
openssl not found

👉 Fix:

RUN apk add --no-cache openssl-dev
🔥 MASTER CHEAT CODE (MOST IMPORTANT)

If many errors come:

RUN apk add --no-cache build-base python3

👉 This solves 80% of cases 🔥

🧠 REAL DEVOPS TRUTH

👉 Nobody memorizes all dependencies
👉 We debug from errors

⚡ PRO WORKFLOW (HOW SENIOR ENGINEERS WORK)
Write minimal Dockerfile
Build
See error
Add missing package
Repeat

👉 This is called:
Iterative Debugging

🚀 BONUS: Smart Guessing Trick
If you see in project:
Dependency Type	Add
Image processing	libjpeg-dev, zlib-dev
DB drivers	postgresql-dev, mysql-dev
Crypto	openssl-dev
ML/Data	build-base, gfortran
